  "prompt": "A top-down schematic floor plan of a compact 5-pyeong (approximately 16.5㎡) computer cluster workspace designed for 21 PCs. The room has a ceiling-mounted air conditioner at the top center, a window to the left, and a visible door at the bottom. On the left wall, there is a vertical stack of shelves (기존선반) and below it, a newly added long table labeled '에어컨 서큘레이터'. PCs are arranged in three primary zones: 1) along the left wall shelves (6–9 units), 2) horizontally along the bottom center in two rows (12–14 units), and 3) one zone at the top right corner for main PC, network hub, NAS, and UPS. Also shown is a circular exhaust fan at the top right wall. Use clear color blocks and Korean labels. Emphasize airflow direction with blue arrows, power flow with red lines, and label circuit zones. Background should remain minimal, blueprint-style.",
  "size": "1024x768"
}
